pullComment

public java.lang.Thread pullComment(java.lang.String esID,
                                    java.lang.String index,
                                    java.lang.String query)
This method will pull a single comment and set the commentModel field of this CommentSearch object to be equal to the 0th element in an array list of the sources of the hits. If the number of hits is greater than one, then the commentModel field is not updated.

Parameters:
esID - the elastic search id of the comment
index - the index in which the comment is found
Returns:

pull

public java.lang.Thread pull(BrowseActivity topLevelActivity,
                             java.lang.String queryDSL,
                             java.lang.String index,
                             java.lang.String commentID,
                             CommentListModel browseModel,
                             Cache mCache)
Pulls the data from ElasticSearchResponse and sets it up for sorting on a new thread.

Parameters:
topLevelActivity - An instance of the activity showing top-level comments.
queryDSL - The query to be searched.
index - The index of the comment.
commentID - The ID of the comment.
Returns:
thread The thread which the search will be ran on.
